cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new parallel corpus for natural language processing research.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the corpus can be used for developing and testing keyword-assignment software.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the corpus can be used for training and testing multi-label classification algorithms.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the corpus can be used for developing and testing text analysis software across different languages.
- cs.DL (Deep Learning) is less likely but still possible as the corpus can be used for training and testing neural machine translation models.
